# Cross-Agent Rules

Always follow these protocols. Full details: [.cursor/workflow/](../workflow/) and [docs/STANDARD.md](../../docs/STANDARD.md).

## Communication

Use artifact-first messages per [communication-protocol.md](../workflow/communication-protocol.md):
- Include date, tier, phase, related doc paths
- Record decisions in versioned docs, not chat-only

## Handoffs

Before transferring work between agents, complete the checklist in [handoff-procedures.md](../workflow/handoff-procedures.md) and verify [quality-gates.yaml](../workflow/quality-gates.yaml).

| Transition | Gate key |
|------------|----------|
| Manager → Architect | `manager_to_architect` |
| Architect → Manager (escalation) | `architect_to_manager` |
| Architect → Developer | `architect_to_developer` |
| Developer → QA | `developer_to_qa` |
| QA → Developer (failure) | `qa_to_developer` |
| QA → DevOps | `qa_to_devops` |
| DevOps → Manager | `devops_to_manager` |

## Escalation

Classify issues P0–P3 per [escalation-matrix.md](../workflow/escalation-matrix.md). P0/P1 block release until resolved or explicitly accepted by Manager.

## Documentation

All new docs require YAML frontmatter (title, version, created, updated, owner, reviewers, status, tags, audience, tier). No `TODO`, `TBD`, or `fill in later` in `approved` docs.

## Tier Model

Detect tier via [scaling-indicators.yaml](../workflow/scaling-indicators.yaml). Skip docs listed under `simplify.skip_docs` for T1 only when tier exception is logged in sprint notes.

## Quality Gates (summary)

- Lint errors: 0 before QA handoff
- Unit coverage: T1 60%, T2 80%, T3 85%
- Open P0/P1 defects: 0 before deploy
- Gate artifacts: `status: approved`

## Knowledge Transfer

Schedule KT per [knowledge-transfer.md](../workflow/knowledge-transfer.md) on architect→developer handoff and major releases.

## Agent Playbooks

| Role | Playbook |
|------|----------|
| Manager | [manager/RULE.md](../agents/manager/RULE.md) |
| Architect | [architect/RULE.md](../agents/architect/RULE.md) |
| Developer | [developer/RULE.md](../agents/developer/RULE.md) |
| QA | [qa/RULE.md](../agents/qa/RULE.md) |
| DevOps | [devops/RULE.md](../agents/devops/RULE.md) |

## Validation Before Task Complete

- [ ] Handoff gate checked if phase transition
- [ ] Docs cross-linked and frontmatter valid
- [ ] Escalation severity assigned if blocked
- [ ] Success criteria from role playbook met
